        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 7:16PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 716 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Thornton, or 16 miles north of Denver, moving east at 5 mph. Another
strong storm was located over Broomfield.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree branches and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Thornton, northeastern Westminster, Broomfield, northern Commerce
City, northern Northglenn, Brighton, Lafayette, Louisville, Todd
Creek and Henderson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rain is occurring with this storm and may lead to flooding. Do
not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
